  "intro": "State verbs often use the imperfect because they describe conditions, knowledge, feelings, possession, or wants in the past. They give background instead of a single finished event.",
  "overview": {
    "body": "Common state verbs include estar, tener, saber, conocer, querer, necesitar, creer, and entender. In the imperfect they describe what was true at the time.",
